'''Adil Douiri''' ({{lang-ar|عادل الدويري}}; born 16 November 1963 in [[Rabat]]) is a Moroccan politician, businessman and [[venture capital]]ist.
== Personal life ==
He is the son of Mhamed Douiri who was also a Minister and a daughter of [[Ahmed Balafrej]].<ref name=eco>{{cite news|title=La famille, le plus grand parti du Maroc|url=http://www.lavieeco.com/news/politique/la-famille-le-plus-grand-parti-du-maroc-5450.html|accessdate=6 December 2013|newspaper=La vie économique|date=18 February 2005|author=Karim Douichi}}</ref> He is also the cousin of [[Fouad Douiri]].
== Career ==
In 1992, he founded the Casablanca Finance Group.<ref>[https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=59453991&privcapId=44306609 "Adil Douiri"], ''Bloomberg''. Accessed 23 March 2016.</ref> Between 2002 and 2007, he was the [[Minister of Tourism]] in the cabinet of [[Driss Jettou]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Le nouveau gouvernement|url=http://www.maghress.com/fr/leconomiste/44700|accessdate=6 December 2013|newspaper=l'économiste|date=8 November 2002}}</ref>
