{{Infobox member of the Knesset |image = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1941|9|21|df=y}} |birth_place = |Year of Aliyah = |death_date = |death_place = |Knesset(s) = [[Israeli legislative election, 1984|11]] |party1 = [[Likud]] |partyyears1 = 1988 }}
'''David Mor''' ({{lang-he|דוד מור}}, born 21 September 1941) is an [[Israel]]i businessman and former politician who briefly served as a member of the [[Knesset]] for [[Likud]] in 1988.
==Biography== During the 1980s he was chairman of the board of directors of the government development company, Shikun VePituah. He won on the Likud list for the [[Israeli legislative election, 1984|1984 elections]], but failed to win a seat. However, he entered the Knesset on 27 October 1988, replacing [[Michael Reisser]],<ref>[https://www.knesset.gov.il/mk/eng/mkindexbyknesset_eng.asp?knesset=11 Knesset Members in the Eleventh Knesset] Knesset website</ref> who had been killed in a car crash. However, he lost his seat in the [[Israeli legislative election, 1988|November elections]].
Today he lives in [[Savyon]] and is married with three children. He is the father-in-law of [[Amos Mansdorf]].
