'''José Habie Nigrin''' (November 14, 1956 – September 28, 2012), better known as '''Joe''' or '''Joey Habie''', was a [[Guatemala]]n businessman. He was the owner of the Liztex Corporation, one of the five largest exporters of fabrics in Latin America. He also owned the [[Tikal Futura]] business and hotel complex in [[Guatemala City]]. Habie died in a helicopter crash in Guatemala City on September 28, 2012. He was the sole occupant of the aircraft.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kcautv.com/story/19669830/one-of-guatemalas-richest-men-dies-in-helicopter|title=One of Guatemala's richest men dies in helicopter|publisher=kcautv.com|accessdate=September 29, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prensalibre.com/noticias/Empresario-perece-caer-helicoptero_0_782921724.html|title=Empresario perece al caer helicóptero|publisher=prensalibre.com|accessdate=September 29, 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929110629/http://prensalibre.com/noticias/Empresario-perece-caer-helicoptero_0_782921724.html|archivedate=September 29, 2012|df=}} (Spanish)</ref>

