{{Infobox person | image = Mirko Ehrmann and his family..jpg | imagesize = | caption = Mirko Hermann with his family. | name = Mirko Hermann | birth_name = Mirko Emerich Hermann | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1868|08|05}} | birth_place = [[Osijek]], [[Austria-Hungary|Austro-Hungarian monarchy]], (now [[Croatia]]) | death_date = {{Death date and age|df=yes|1927|04|02|1868|08|05}} | death_place = [[Zagreb]], [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]], (now [[Croatia]]) | occupation = [[Business magnate|Industrialist]], [[businessman]] | alma_mater = | relations = | spouse = | children = | nationality = [[Croats|Croat]] }}
'''Mirko Hermann''' (5 August 1868 – 2 April 1927) was a [[Croatia]]n industrialist, businessman and member of the [[Freemasonry]] in [[Osijek]], Croatia.
Hermann was born in Osijek on 5 August 1868. He was raised in a Croatian [[Jews|Jewish]] family of David Hermann. Hermann finished elementary and high school in Osijek. He attended and graduated from the [[University of Veterinary Medicine Vienna]] and University of [[University of Natural Resources and Life Sciences, Vienna]]. For a short period of time, after graduation, Hermann worked in [[Lika]] and later moved to [[Čepin]] near Osijek. In 1897 Hermann acquired on lease the agricultural estate "Mihajlović". He was also a renowned art collector and a longtime member of the "First Croatian-Slavonian traded company for the sugar industry" in Osijek. Hermann was one of the key renovators of [[Masonic Lodge|Masonic]] activity in Osijek. From 1903 he was a member of the [[Freemasonry]] lodge "Ljubav bližnjega" (''The Neighbour's Love'') and from 1912 founder and [[Masonic Lodge Officers|Worshipful Master]] of the lodge "Budnost" (''Vigilance''). Due to disagreements with some members and the internal conflicts in the lodge, caused by new political circumstances after the [[World War I]], Hermann retired from a place of Worshipful Master and left the lodge in 1923.<ref name="os">{{Cite news | language = Croatian | last = Živaković-Kerže | first = Zlata |author2=Nevenka Drahotuski | title = Osječki spomendan 5. kolovoza | pages= | newspaper = [[Osijek]] | date = 2011-08-04 | url = http://www.osijek.hr/index.php/cro/Osijek/Osjecki-spomendan/Osjecki-spomendan-5.-kolovoza | accessdate = 2013-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | language = Croatian | last = Matičić | first = Slaven | title = Masoni u Osijeku: Jedna od najjačih loža u cijeloj regiji | pages = | newspaper = Kultura u [[Osijek]]u - www.kultura-osijek.com | date = 2012-11-24 | url = http://www.kultura-osijek.com/urbana-kultura-i-stil/masoni-u-osijeku-jedna-od-najjacih-loza-u-cijeloj-regiji | accessdate = 2013-05-23 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130616154815/http://www.kultura-osijek.com/urbana-kultura-i-stil/masoni-u-osijeku-jedna-od-najjacih-loza-u-cijeloj-regiji | archivedate = 2013-06-16 | df = }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | language = Croatian | last = | first = | title = Otvorenje izložbe OSTAVŠTINA OSJEČKE SLOBODNOZIDARSKE LOŽE "BUDNOST" u Hrvatskom povijesnom muzeju u Zagrebu | pages= | newspaper = www.culturenet.hr | date = 2004 | url = http://www.culturenet.hr/default.aspx?id=3932 | accessdate = 2013-05-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | language = Croatian | last = | first = | title = Zbirka slikarstva 20. stoljeća, I. polovica | pages = | newspaper = Galerija likovnih umjetnosti Osijek - www.gluo.hr | date = 2004 | url = http://www.gluo.hr/zs20.html | accessdate = 2013-05-23 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130616154745/http://www.gluo.hr/zs20.html | archivedate = 2013-06-16 | df = }}</ref> Hermann was legal guardian of Terezija Svećenski, mother of [[Louis Svećenski]], until her death.<ref name=essekeri>{{cite news|url=http://essekeri.hr/bio/73-lujo-svecenski|title=Biografija: Lujo Svećenski|publisher=Essekeri|work=essekeri.hr|language=Croatian}}</ref> He died in [[Zagreb]] on 2 April 1927 and was buried at the [[Mirogoj Cemetery]].<ref name="os"/><ref>{{hr icon}} Gradska groblja Zagreb: Mirko Hermann, Mirogoj Ž-8-I-61</ref>
