==Professional career==
Emma Rasolovoahangy is the founding president of Petromad (Mauritius) Limited.<ref>{{url
| 1 = http://www.africaintelligence.com/ION/who-s-who/2007/02/17/emma-rasolovoahangy,26430024-ART
| 2 = UNITED STATES-MADAGASCAR - Emma Rasolovoahangy - The Indian Ocean Newsletter
}}</ref> Petromad holds rights to the Bezaha exploration located in the Morondava Oil Basin, south-west of Madagascar.<ref name="Madagate">{{cite news
 |title       = Madagascar: le pétrole de tous les dangers!
 |url         = http://www.madagate.com/chronique/322-madagascar-le-petrole-de-tous-les-dangers-.html
 |accessdate  = {{date|13 July 2013}}
 |newspaper   = Madagate
 |date        = {{date|8 August 2008}}
 |deadurl     = yes
 |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20130222122353/http://madagate.com/chronique/322-madagascar-le-petrole-de-tous-les-dangers-.html
 |archivedate = 22 February 2013
 |df          = 
}}</ref>
She is the first native Madagascan to win a bid for a concession to search for oil in Madagascar. Since Petromad’s establishment in 2005, more than 300 jobs have been created for Malagasy workers.

==Early life and education==
Emma Rasolovoahangy was born in the city of [[Fianarantsoa]], Madagascar.<ref>{{url
| 1 = http://emma.mg/biography/
| 2 = Biography
}}</ref> She is the second of eight children; both of her parents are teachers. She is married with two children.

Her early education was in Antananarivo. In 1984, she was the captain of the national women’s basketball team. Subsequently, her three months of basic military training led to a junior high teaching assignment in a remote rural village. In 1991, she majored in Natural Gas Engineering and graduated with a Master of Science from the Algerian Institute of Petroleum in Algeria. Afterwards, she went to [[Texas A&M University]] in the United States, where she graduated with a Master of Science, Petroleum Engineering and Environmental Engineering in 1994.  Determined to expand her portfolio and skills, she graduated with Master (2000) and Ph.D. degrees in Geophysics (2002) from Stanford University.<ref>{{url
| 1 = http://www.linkedin.com/in/erasolovoahangy
| 2 = Linkedin
}}</ref>

